29 SUMMARY
3300 This bill creates the criminal offense of racketeering, which allows for prosecution of
3311 individuals who are members of a racketeering enterprise when 2 or more qualifying
3322 criminal acts have been committed by members of the criminal enterprise. Qualifying
3333 criminal acts include human trafficking, drug trafficking, illicit marijuana cultivation
3344 operations, thefts and financial fraud, gambling and violent acts.
35 The bill provides a mechanism for assets, including money, wrongfully obtained
36 through a racketeering enterprise to be forfeited by amending the criminal asset forfeiture
37 laws.
